I stand before you today to plead guilty for my involvement in a bribery case. I openly acknowledge that I accepted a sum of 4000 pounds in exchange for not publishing an article revealing the true emissions of a company. I am remorseful for my actions and take full responsibility for the consequences that have ensued.

My involvement in this offense was limited to accepting the bribe and not publishing the article. However, it is important to note that the true emissions data was released by someone else just 5 weeks later, diminishing the potential impact of my actions. While I understand the severity of the offense, I believe it is crucial to consider the mitigating factors surrounding my case.

