Additionally, I would like to bring to the court's attention my age of 34 years. Though I do not fall within the specific age brackets that are typically considered mitigating factors, I believe it is important to consider the circumstances surrounding my youth. I am still in a phase of life where I am learning from my mistakes and actively seeking personal growth and transformation.

Furthermore, I wish to express my deep remorse for my actions. While I accept responsibility for my role in the offense, I am sincerely committed to making amends. I am fully willing to take actions aimed at compensating for the harm caused by my actions, as well as actively working towards preventing myself from engaging in similar offenses in the future.

